  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a medium saucepan, combine the butter, onion, and garlic. Cook over medium heat until the onion is translucent, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add the ground almonds, thyme, salt, and pepper to the saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.",
    "Remove the saucepan from the heat and stir in the Parmesan cheese until melted.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the cream and egg yolks until smooth.",
    "Add the cream mixture to the saucepan and stir to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13-inch comal or baking dish.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the casserole is set.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for 5 minutes before serving.",
    "Garnish with fresh thyme, if desired."
  ],
